node.text:
I know, I know.. I’ve gone way too long in life without experiencing the magic that is Disney. I, like many, haven’t been able to celebrate my birthday in two years so I thought this was a good time to see some of my best friends and get a little birthday/ life celebrating/friend celebrating in.

Best day ever. 
Disney land is open you guys!! 
@disneyparksIt’s Disney so it’s super clean and respectful of guidelines and keeping everyone safe. It’s only open about 30 percent occupancy so it’s a great time to go. The new Star Wars ride is next level and yes I bought a light saber.. I also brought a rainbow Micky kids hat and had my name embroidered in the back like a 10 year old. 
I needed some pure, light, joy. Thank you @disneyland @disneyparksblog

node.text: Sometimes you meet people and they change your life.. I’m so lucky for the friends I have.. they have helped me heal, helped me grow, loved me through the high life and the low times.. @brezofficial you are a blessing to all who know you.. and I’m that EXTRA friend who is always on one but you love me anyway... and I love you and when you told me you were obsessed with my massage chair.. well.. what are birthdays for if not an excuse to be extra. Wish I could have been here for this but it was still the perfect surprise to remind you that you deserve EVERYTHING in life. God made you and God brought us together and now we are ride or die for each other and your family is mine and vice versa. Till the end xxx love you. @bodyfriend for my best friend.

node.text: To everyone asking about my new Pez dispenser scar on my neck... A couple of months ago I was told I needed an emergency surgery or I was risking becoming paralyzed... I had herniated two discs doing stunts, and they were close to severing my spinal chord. I was in chronic pain and yet couldn’t feel my arms... Thank you Dr Bray for everything you did and for allowing me to keep working and doing what I love. I am forever in your debt. And to anyone asking why I let them video it.. Did you not watch that Greys anatomy episode where they left a towel in a patient?? Also I wanted to see what happens when we go under.

node.text:
Thank you to everyone who made yesterday so special. I haven’t celebrated my birthday in 2 years like many of you and I wasn’t planning on doing so( it was in March ).
The thing about that is I’m not sure there is a greater way to practice gratitude than by spending a day with the people you love and adore, bathing in the gratitude of the present moment and thanking god for another day. 
Despite how each day turns out, despite the ups and downs, the easy days and the challenging days are all made easier when you share it all with a family, chosen or other. 
Thank you to @newportyachts who somehow managed to organize this so last minute, @thepicnic.collective for the beautiful surprise decorations and spread, @casamigos for hooking us up with the drinks and @high90s for the flower.

node.text:
Happy Father’s Day to all the amazing fathers out there. My thoughts and love go to all who never had a dad or lost one too soon and to each of you who can’t be with your dad on this day.. I have had chosen fathers my whole life, and I have had friends who have felt instantly like long lost family, who have provided me a judgement free, safe, supportive unconditional kind of love. Not pictured is Anthony Cornish who was the closest thing I had to a father growing up. Despite only being with my mother a few short years, we continued to have communication into my adulthood, sadly he passed away right before I got my job at MTV, right before i broke out, but he is who inspired my Koi sleeve. 
The first slide is one of the most important men in my life, my brother, my father, my son, my best friend Vin. The second is my step dad of many years Roderick who has been fixing two broken iPhones to make one working one despite me offering to send a 2 new ones.. at first I thought it was adorable and obviously not possible with phones these days.. but well.. he got it working 😂. The rest are my friends who are wonderful inspiring fathers who restored my faith in Dads. X
